A printed federal government document titled ‚ÄúReport on Risk Analysis in Civil Protection 2012‚Äù looked at two potential hazards the country could face: 1) Flooding rivers fed by mountain run off, and 2) potential SARS-like pandemic.
Described 1 to 1 today‚Äôs situation ‚Äì in 2012!
The 88-page government report, beginning on page 55, explicitly assesses the potential pandemic risks and warns of catastrophic consequences that could unfold. It describes almost 1 to 1 what is happening today. Particularly macabre is that the corona virus is explicitly named and that the outbreak would start in ‚ÄúFebruary‚Äù and that the first two cases would appear in North Rhine Westphalia and Southern Germany!
Moreover it describes the major economic changes¬† and the possible encroachment of fundamental rights that would occur. The event is also seen unfolding in February in Asia and spreading to Germany just weeks later (see 2.4).
